{
  "texts": [
    "Unfortunately, these questions fall outside the scope of this paper.",
    "Our aim, here, is just to highlight the fact that, unlike other kinds of affective artifacts that are typically considered in the debate, affective artificial agents present some difficulties when it comes to their transparency.",
    "Further reflections are needed to evaluate whether and to what extent affective artificial agents' emotional transparency is compatible with the ethical and normative requirements AI systems should comply with.",
    "This paper provided an analysis of affective artificial agents starting from the existing literature on affective artifacts.",
    "First, we have shown how affective artificial agents are endowed with specific forms of agency and fail to extend our sense of self in the way standard affective artifacts typically do."
  ]
}